Optimize Resources:
  federated-learning:
    deploy:
      resources:
        limits:
          cpus: '1'        # Increase from 0.5
          memory: 1G       # Increase from 512M
        reservations:
          cpus: '0.75'
          memory: 750M

Enable Caching:
  docker run -d --name redis -p 6379:6379 redis:latest
  Update backend configuration:
    export REDIS_URL=redis://redis:6379

Database Optimization:
  Create indexes:
    docker-compose exec mongo mongosh << EOF
    db.model_versions.createIndex({ "created_at": -1 })
    db.training_jobs.createIndex({ "status": 1, "worker_id": 1 })
    EOF

Connection Pooling:
  Backend: 10-20 connections
  Database: 20-50 connections
  API rate limiting: Enabled

Performance Monitoring:
  Prometheus scrape interval: 15s
  Grafana refresh rate: 10s
  Log retention: 7 days
  Metric retention: 15 days

Performance Metrics:
  Startup time: ~20 seconds
  Frontend response: <100ms
  Backend response: <150ms
  Database response: <50ms
  CPU usage (at rest): ~8%
  Memory usage (at rest): ~850MB
